post_text: Hancock County Schools will now be operating under the seamless summer option through December 31st. This means that all children ages 1-18 will receive free breakfast and free lunch. Children enrolled in traditional learning will receive these meals while attending during the school day. Virtual students and children ages 1-18 that are not enrolled in Hancock County Schools can continue to pickup a week of breakfast and lunch meals on Wednesday’s from 9:00-10:00 a.m. at Hancock Elementary or Hancock Middle/High. Please drive around to the kitchen door and ring the doorbell. The cafeteria staff will bring the meal bags to your vehicle. This service will be provided until further notice.

post_text:
Attention Parents and Guardians,
On Wednesday, Aug 19th, school buses will run their morning route picking up children that do not have internet at home AND have been in contact with the school about not having internet. Those children will ride the bus to school and be dropped off at 8:00. Children will go to their Homeroom teacher. The teacher will help them download work and show them how to access Google Classroom. The bus will pick children back up at 9:00am and take them home.

Also—if you are interested in having meals delivered from the school, (not food boxes from the mail), you must complete the form @hancockcountyschools.com OR call your child’s school. Meals can only be delivered by buses with a parent/guardian request. Meals will be delivered to homes between 9:00-11:00 on Wednesdays.

**Meal pickup at the both the elementary and middle high school is from 11:00-12:00 on Wednesdays.

post_text:
Hello 3rd and 5th grade students,

We want to invite you a virtual practice session on August 13th at 2:00pm. This practice session is optional. If you haven’t picked up your materials or been in contact with your teacher, it is okay. If you can, we would appreciate you attending. The Google Meet will be a time for you to say Hello to your ELA and Math teachers and a time for the school to test the system.

Steps for the Virtual Practice

1. On your device, go to the internet and then go to www.classroom.google.com
2. Click join a class
3. Use your hancockcountyschools.com email and password to join. (This info is in a folder in your backpack from school)
4. Choose your ELA/Reading Classroom
5. Look for further instructions on your Google Meet in the “Stream”

HCES 2020-21 KINDERGARTEN REGISTRATION AND SCREENING
May 8, 2020|HCES
For parents of children that will turn 5 on or before August 15, 2020

•Kindergarten Registration packets will be available for pick-up at the Hancock County Elementary School beginning July 8th, 2020.

•Mandatory Kindergarten Screenings will be given to students during the first week of school in the fall.

Required Documents:

•Child’s Birth Certificate

•Social Security Card

•Up-to-date Immunization record and Well Child medical examination

•Custodial Documentation (if applicable)

Immunization records and well-child examinations can be obtained from the Hancock County Health Department.

More information will be available closer to the beginning of the 2020-21 school year. Please continue to check the Hancock County Schools website (www.hancockcountyschools.com) for up to date information concerning the school district and any changes due to the COVID-19 state and local social distancing requirements

post_text: Hancock County School Nutrition Program would like to thank the cafeteria staff for all of their hard work and dedication in feeding the students of Hancock County. These ladies sent out over 16,000 breakfast and lunch meals since the beginning of the COVID-19 emergency. We would also like to thank all the administrators, teachers, aides, custodians, bus drivers, community members, and volunteers that assisted with deliveries, meal prep, and contacting parents for sign-ups for the Emergency Meals To You Program. Over 500 households and just under 1000 children were signed up over a 5 day period.
